Alstom May Build Belgrade Subway on French Support, Tanjug Says

-- B y   M i s h a   S a v i c
-- 
2011-04-11T07:12:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-11/alstom-may-build-belgrade-subway-on-french-support-tanjug-says.html
A strategic partnership agreement
between Serbia and France negotiated by respective presidents in
Paris last week may position  Alstom SA (ALO)  to build Belgrade’s first
subway network,  Tanjug  news agency reported, citing sources
familiar with the talks.  Nicolas Sarkozy and  Boris Tadic  have agreed that respective
governments and the municipal authorities in the Serbian capital
agree “financial modalities” of the infrastructure project
estimated to cost between 1 billion euros ($1.45 billion) and
1.2 billion euros, according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Misha Savic in Belgrade at 
 msavic2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net  